366 void player_activity::deserialize( const JsonObject &data )
367 {
368  data.allow_omitted_members();
369  std::string tmptype;
370  int tmppos = 0;
371 
372  bool is_obsolete = false;
373  std::set<std::string> obs_activities {
374  "ACT_MAKE_ZLAVE" // Remove after 0.F
375  };
376  if( !data.read( "type", tmptype ) ) {
377  // Then it's a legacy save.
378  int tmp_type_legacy = data.get_int( "type" );
379  deserialize_legacy_type( tmp_type_legacy, type );
380  } else if( !obs_activities.count( tmptype ) ) {
381  type = activity_id( tmptype );
382  } else {
383  is_obsolete = true;
384  }
385 
386  if( type.is_null() ) {
387  return;
388  }
389 
390  const bool has_actor = activity_actors::deserialize_functions.find( type ) !=
391  activity_actors::deserialize_functions.end();
392 
393  // Handle migration of pre-activity_actor activities
394  // ACT_MIGRATION_CANCEL will clear the backlog and reset npc state
395  // this may cause inconvenience but should avoid any lasting damage to npcs
396  if( is_obsolete || ( has_actor && ( data.has_null( "actor" ) || !data.has_member( "actor" ) ) ) ) {
397  type = ACT_MIGRATION_CANCEL;
398  actor = std::make_unique<migration_cancel_activity_actor>();
399  } else {
400  data.read( "actor", actor );
401  }
402 
403  if( !data.read( "position", tmppos ) ) {
404  tmppos = INT_MIN; // If loading a save before position existed, hope.
405  }
406 
407  data.read( "moves_total", moves_total );
408  data.read( "moves_left", moves_left );
409  data.read( "interruptable", interruptable );
410  data.read( "interruptable_with_kb", interruptable_with_kb );
411  data.read( "index", index );
412  position = tmppos;
413  data.read( "coords", coords );
414  data.read( "coord_set", coord_set );
415  data.read( "name", name );
416  data.read( "targets", targets );
417  data.read( "placement", placement );
418  data.read( "relative_placement", relative_placement );
419  values = data.get_int_array( "values" );
420  str_values = data.get_string_array( "str_values" );
421  data.read( "auto_resume", auto_resume );
422  data.read( "monsters", monsters );
423 
424 }

467 void SkillLevel::deserialize( const JsonObject &data )
468 {
469  data.allow_omitted_members();
470  data.read( "level", _level );
471  data.read( "exercise", _exercise );
472  if( _level < 0 ) {
473  _level = 0;
474  _exercise = 0;
475  }
476  if( _exercise < 0 ) {
477  _exercise = 0;
478  }
479  data.read( "istraining", _isTraining );
480  data.read( "rustaccumulator", _rustAccumulator );
481  if( !data.read( "lastpracticed", _lastPracticed ) ) {
482  _lastPracticed = calendar::start_of_game;
483  }
484  data.read( "knowledgeLevel", _knowledgeLevel );
485  if( _knowledgeLevel < _level ) {
486  _knowledgeLevel = _level;
487  }
488  data.read( "knowledgeExperience", _knowledgeExperience );
489  if( _knowledgeLevel == _level && _knowledgeExperience < _exercise ) {
490  _knowledgeExperience = _exercise;
491  }
492 }

549 void Character::trait_data::deserialize( const JsonObject &data )
550 {
551  data.allow_omitted_members();
552  data.read( "key", key );
553 
554  //Remove after 0.G
555  if( data.has_int( "charge" ) ) {
556  charge = time_duration::from_turns( data.get_int( "charge" ) );
557  } else {
558  data.read( "charge", charge );
559  }
560  data.read( "powered", powered );
561  data.read( "show_sprite", show_sprite );
562  if( data.has_member( "variant-parent" ) ) {
563  trait_id parent;
564  std::string variant_id;
565 
566  data.read( "variant-parent", parent );
567  data.read( "variant-id", variant_id );
568 
569  // No parent == nowhere to look up this variant. It's effectively lost
570  if( !parent.is_valid() ) {
571  return;
572  }
573  variant = parent->variant( variant_id );
574  }
575 }

1116  ( weapon->has_flag( flag_BIONIC_WEAPON ) || weapon->has_flag( flag_BIONIC_GUN ) ) &&
1117  weapon->has_flag( flag_NO_UNWIELD ) && !weapon->ethereal;
1118 
1119  const auto find_parent = [this]( bionic_id & bio_id ) {
1120  for( const bionic &bio : *this->my_bionics ) {
1121  if( std::find( bio.id->included_bionics.begin(), bio.id->included_bionics.end(),
1122  bio_id ) != bio.id->included_bionics.end() ) {
1123  return bio.get_uid();

1144  }

1660  std::string grab_typestr = "OBJECT_NONE";
1661  if( grab_point.x != 0 || grab_point.y != 0 ) {
1662  grab_typestr = "OBJECT_VEHICLE";
1663  data.read( "grab_type", grab_typestr );
1664  } else {
1665  // we just want to read, but ignore grab_type
1666  std::string fake;
1667  data.read( "grab_type", fake );
1668  }
1669 
1670  // On Visual Studio array iterators are not pointers, so prevent clang-tidy
1671  // from converting this to a pointer type.
1672  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(readability-qualified-auto)
1673  const auto iter = std::find( obj_type_name.begin(), obj_type_name.end(), grab_typestr );
1674  grab( iter == obj_type_name.end() ?
1675  object_type::NONE : static_cast<object_type>(
1676  std::distance( obj_type_name.begin(), iter ) ),
1677  grab_point );
1678 
1679  data.read( "magic", magic );
1680 
1681  calc_mutation_levels();
1682  drench_mut_calc();
1683  std::string scen_ident = "(null)";
1684  if( data.read( "scenario", scen_ident ) && string_id<scenario>( scen_ident ).is_valid() ) {
1685  set_scenario( &string_id<scenario>( scen_ident ).obj() );
1686 
1687  if( !get_scenario()->allowed_start( start_location ) ) {
1688  start_location = get_scenario()->random_start_location();
1689  }
1690  } else {
1691  const scenario *generic_scenario = scenario::generic();
1692

1694  scen_ident.c_str(), generic_scenario->ident().c_str() );

1696  }

1699  valid_autolearn_skills->clear(); // Invalidates the cache
1700 
1701  items_identified.clear();
1702  data.read( "items_identified", items_identified );
1703 
1704  data.read( "translocators", translocators );
1705 
1706  std::vector<int> tmpmissions;
1707  if( data.read( "active_missions", tmpmissions ) ) {
1708  active_missions = mission::to_ptr_vector( tmpmissions );
1709  }
1710  if( data.read( "failed_missions", tmpmissions ) ) {
1711  failed_missions = mission::to_ptr_vector( tmpmissions );
1712  }
1713  if( data.read( "completed_missions", tmpmissions ) ) {
1714  completed_missions = mission::to_ptr_vector( tmpmissions );
1715  }
1716 
1717  int tmpactive_mission = 0;
1718  if( data.read( "active_mission", tmpactive_mission ) ) {
1719  if( tmpactive_mission != -1 ) {
1720  active_mission = mission::find( tmpactive_mission );
1721  }
1722  }
1723 
1724  // Normally there is only one player character loaded, so if a mission that is assigned to
1725  // another character (not the current one) fails, the other character(s) are not informed.
1726  // We must inform them when they get loaded the next time.
1727  // Only active missions need checking, failed/complete will not change anymore.
1728  const auto last = std::remove_if( active_missions.begin(),
1729  active_missions.end(), []( mission const * m ) {
1730  return m->has_failed();
1731  } );
1732  std::copy( last, active_missions.end(), std::back_inserter( failed_missions ) );
1733  active_missions.erase( last, active_missions.end() );
1734  if( active_mission && active_mission->has_failed() ) {
1735  if( active_missions.empty() ) {
1736  active_mission = nullptr;
1737  } else {
1738  active_mission = active_missions.front();
1739  }
1740  }

1742  data.read( "show_map_memory", show_map_memory );
1743 
1744  for( JsonArray pair : data.get_array( "assigned_invlet" ) ) {

1750  inv->json_load_invcache( data.get_member( "invcache" ) );
1751  }
1752 
1753  data.read( "calorie_diary", calorie_diary );
1754 
1755  data.read( "preferred_aiming_mode", preferred_aiming_mode );
1756 
1757  if( data.has_member( "power_prev_turn" ) ) {
1758  data.read( "power_prev_turn", power_prev_turn );
1759  }
1760

1805  cbm_recharge = static_cast<cbm_recharge_rule>( tmprecharge );

1807  // deserialize the flags so they can be changed between save games
1808  for( const auto &rule : ally_rule_strs ) {
1809  bool tmpflag = false;

1814  } else {
1815  clear_flag( rule.second.rule );
1816  }

1818  if( tmpflag ) {
1819  set_flag( rule.second.rule );
1820  } else {
1821  clear_flag( rule.second.rule );
1822  }
1823  data.read( "override_enable_" + rule.first, tmpflag );
1824  if( tmpflag ) {
1825  enable_override( rule.second.rule );
1826  } else {
1827  disable_override( rule.second.rule );
1828  }
1829  data.read( "override_" + rule.first, tmpflag );
1830  if( tmpflag ) {
1831  set_override( rule.second.rule );
1832  } else {
1833  clear_override( rule.second.rule );
1834  }
1835 
1836  // This and the following two entries are for legacy save game handling.
1837  // "avoid_combat" was renamed "follow_close" to better reflect behavior.
1838  if( data.has_member( "rule_avoid_combat" ) ) {
1839  data.read( "rule_avoid_combat", tmpflag );
1840  if( tmpflag ) {
1841  set_flag( ally_rule::follow_close );
1842  } else {
1843  clear_flag( ally_rule::follow_close );
1844  }
1845  }
1846  if( data.has_member( "override_enable_avoid_combat" ) ) {
1847  data.read( "override_enable_avoid_combat", tmpflag );
1848  if( tmpflag ) {
1849  enable_override( ally_rule::follow_close );
1850  } else {
1851  disable_override( ally_rule::follow_close );
1852  }
1853  }
1854  if( data.has_member( "override_avoid_combat" ) ) {
1855  data.read( "override_avoid_combat", tmpflag );
1856  if( tmpflag ) {
1857  set_override( ally_rule::follow_close );
1858  } else {
1859  clear_override( ally_rule::follow_close );
1860  }
1861  }
1862  }
1863 
1864  data.read( "pickup_whitelist", *pickup_whitelist );
1865 }

3780 
3781  // TEMPORARY until 0.F
3782  if( savegame_loading_version < 31 ) {
3783  if( jsin.has_object( "effects" ) ) {
3784  // Because JSON requires string keys we need to convert back to our bp keys
3785  std::unordered_map<std::string, std::unordered_map<std::string, effect>> tmp_map;
3786  jsin.read( "effects", tmp_map );
3787  int key_num = 0;
3788  for( const auto &maps : tmp_map ) {
3789  const efftype_id id( maps.first );
3790  if( !id.is_valid() ) {
3791  debugmsg( "Invalid effect: %s", id.c_str() );
3792  continue;
3793  }

3795  if( !( std::istringstream( i.first ) >> key_num ) ) {
3796  key_num = 0;
3797  }
3798  const bodypart_str_id &bp = convert_bp( static_cast<body_part>( key_num ) );
3799  const effect &e = i.second;
3800 
3801  ( *effects )[id][bp] = e;
3802  on_effect_int_change( id, e.get_intensity(), bp );
3803  }
3804  }
3805  }
3806  } else {
3807  jsin.read( "effects", *effects );
3808  }
3809 
3810  jsin.read( "values", values );
3811  // potentially migrate some values
3812  for( std::pair<std::string, std::string> migration : get_globals().migrations ) {
3813  if( values.count( migration.first ) != 0 ) {
3814  auto extracted = values.extract( migration.first );
3815  extracted.key() = migration.second;
3816  values.insert( std::move( extracted ) );
3817  }
3818  }
3819 
3820  jsin.read( "damage_over_time_map", damage_over_time_map );
3821

3823  jsin.read( "dodges_left", num_dodges );

3825  jsin.read( "num_dodges_bonus", num_dodges_bonus );

3828  jsin.read( "armor_bonus", armor_bonus );
3829  } else {
3830  // Legacy load conversion, remove after 0.H releases
3831  float bash_bonus = 0;
3832  float cut_bonus = 0;
3833  float bullet_bonus = 0;
3834  jsin.read( "armor_bash_bonus", bash_bonus );

3915 void mm_submap::serialize( JsonOut &jsout ) const
3916 {
3917  jsout.start_array();
3918 
3919  // Uses RLE for compression.
3920 
3921  memorized_tile last;
3922  int num_same = 1;
3923 
3924  const auto write_seq = [&]() {
3925  jsout.start_array();
3926  jsout.write( num_same );
3927  jsout.write( last.symbol );
3928  jsout.write( last.ter_id );
3929  jsout.write( static_cast<int>( last.ter_subtile ) );
3930  jsout.write( static_cast<int>( last.ter_rotation ) );
3931  if( !last.get_dec_id().empty() ) {
3932  jsout.write( last.dec_id );
3933  jsout.write( static_cast<int>( last.dec_subtile ) );
3934  jsout.write( static_cast<int>( last.dec_rotation ) );
3935  }
3936  jsout.end_array();
3937  };
3938 
3939  for( size_t y = 0; y < SEEY; y++ ) {
3940  for( size_t x = 0; x < SEEX; x++ ) {
3941  const memorized_tile &elem = get_tile( point_sm_ms( x, y ) );
3942  if( x == 0 && y == 0 ) {
3943  last = elem;
3944  continue;
3945  }
3946  if( last == elem ) {
3947  num_same += 1;
3948  continue;
3949  }
3950  write_seq();
3951  num_same = 1;
3952  last = elem;
3953  }
3954  }
3955  write_seq();
3956 
3957  jsout.end_array();
3958 }

3960 void mm_submap::deserialize( int version, const JsonArray &ja )
3961 {

3963 
3964  // Uses RLE for compression.
3965  memorized_tile tile;
3966  size_t remaining = 0;
3967 
3968  for( size_t y = 0; y < SEEY; y++ ) {
3969  for( size_t x = 0; x < SEEX; x++ ) {
3970  if( remaining > 0 ) {
3971  remaining -= 1;
3972  } else {
3973  const JsonArray ja_tile = ja.get_array( submap_array_idx++ );
3974  if( version < 1 ) { // legacy, remove after 0.H comes out
3975  std::string id = ja_tile.get_string( 0 );
3976  if( string_starts_with( id, "t_" ) ) {
3977  tile.set_ter_id( std::move( id ) );
3978  tile.set_ter_subtile( ja_tile.get_int( 1 ) );
3979  tile.set_ter_rotation( ja_tile.get_int( 2 ) );
3980  tile.set_dec_id( "" );
3981  tile.set_dec_subtile( 0 );
3982  tile.set_dec_rotation( 0 );
3983  } else {

3985  tile.set_ter_subtile( 0 );
3986  tile.set_ter_rotation( 0 );
3987  tile.set_dec_id( std::move( id ) );
3988  tile.set_dec_subtile( ja_tile.get_int( 1 ) );
3989  const int legacy_rotation = ja_tile.get_int( 2 );
3990  if( string_starts_with( tile.dec_id, "vp_" ) ) {
3991  // legacy vehicle rotation needs to be converted from 0-360 degrees
3992  // to 0-3 tileset rotation
3993  const units::angle legacy_angle = units::from_degrees( legacy_rotation );
3994  tile.set_dec_rotation( angle_to_dir4( 270_degrees - legacy_angle ) );
3995  } else {
3996  tile.set_dec_rotation( legacy_rotation );
3997  }
3998  }
3999  tile.symbol = ja_tile.get_int( 3 );
4000  if( ja_tile.size() > 4 ) {
4001  remaining = ja_tile.get_int( 4 ) - 1;

4004  remaining = ja_tile.get_int( 0 ) - 1;
4005  tile.symbol = ja_tile.get_int( 1 );

4007  tile.ter_subtile = ja_tile.get_int( 3 );

4018  }

4677 void submap::store( JsonOut &jsout ) const
4678 {
4679  jsout.member( "turn_last_touched", last_touched );
4680  jsout.member( "temperature", temperature_mod );
4681 
4682  // Terrain is saved using a simple RLE scheme. Legacy saves don't have
4683  // this feature but the algorithm is backward compatible.
4684  jsout.member( "terrain" );
4685  jsout.start_array();
4686  if( is_uniform() ) {
4687  _write_rle_terrain( jsout, uniform_ter.id().str(), SEEX * SEEY );
4688  jsout.end_array();
4689  return;
4690  }
4691  std::string last_id;
4692  int num_same = 1;
4693  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY; j++ ) {
4694  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(modernize-loop-convert)
4695  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX; i++ ) {
4696  const std::string this_id = m->ter[i][j].obj().id.str();
4697  if( !last_id.empty() ) {
4698  if( this_id == last_id ) {
4699  num_same++;
4700  } else {
4701  if( num_same == 1 ) {
4702  // if there's only one element don't write as an array
4703  jsout.write( last_id );
4704  } else {
4705  _write_rle_terrain( jsout, last_id, num_same );
4706  num_same = 1;
4707  }
4708  last_id = this_id;
4709  }
4710  } else {
4711  last_id = this_id;
4712  }
4713  }
4714  }
4715  // Because of the RLE scheme we have to do one last pass
4716  if( num_same == 1 ) {
4717  jsout.write( last_id );
4718  } else {
4719  jsout.start_array();
4720  jsout.write( last_id );
4721  jsout.write( num_same );
4722  jsout.end_array();
4723  }
4724  jsout.end_array();
4725 
4726  // Write out the radiation array in a simple RLE scheme.
4727  // written in intensity, count pairs
4728  jsout.member( "radiation" );
4729  jsout.start_array();
4730  int lastrad = -1;
4731  int count = 0;
4732  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY; j++ ) {
4733  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX; i++ ) {
4734  const point p( i, j );
4735  // Save radiation, re-examine this because it doesn't look like it works right
4736  int r = get_radiation( p );
4737  if( r == lastrad ) {
4738  count++;
4739  } else {
4740  if( count ) {
4741  jsout.write( count );
4742  }
4743  jsout.write( r );
4744  lastrad = r;
4745  count = 1;
4746  }
4747  }
4748  }
4749  jsout.write( count );
4750  jsout.end_array();
4751 
4752  jsout.member( "furniture" );
4753  jsout.start_array();
4754  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY; j++ ) {
4755  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX; i++ ) {
4756  const point p( i, j );
4757  // Save furniture
4758  if( get_furn( p ) ) {
4759  jsout.start_array();
4760  jsout.write( p.x );
4761  jsout.write( p.y );
4762  jsout.write( get_furn( p ).obj().id );
4763  jsout.end_array();
4764  }
4765  }
4766  }
4767  jsout.end_array();
4768 
4769  jsout.member( "items" );
4770  jsout.start_array();
4771  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY; j++ ) {
4772  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX; i++ ) {
4773  if( m->itm[i][j].empty() ) {
4774  continue;
4775  }
4776  jsout.write( i );
4777  jsout.write( j );
4778  jsout.write( m->itm[i][j] );
4779  }
4780  }
4781  jsout.end_array();
4782 
4783  jsout.member( "traps" );
4784  jsout.start_array();
4785  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY; j++ ) {
4786  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX; i++ ) {
4787  const point p( i, j );
4788  // Save traps
4789  if( get_trap( p ) ) {
4790  jsout.start_array();
4791  jsout.write( p.x );
4792  jsout.write( p.y );
4793  // TODO: jsout should support writing an id like jsout.write( trap_id )
4794  jsout.write( get_trap( p ).id().str() );
4795  jsout.end_array();
4796  }
4797  }
4798  }
4799  jsout.end_array();
4800 
4801  jsout.member( "fields" );
4802  jsout.start_array();
4803  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY; j++ ) {
4804  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX; i++ ) {

4806  if( m->fld[i][j].field_count() > 0 ) {
4807  jsout.write( i );

4894 void submap::load( const JsonValue &jv, const std::string &member_name, int version )
4895 {
4896  ensure_nonuniform();
4897  bool rubpow_update = version < 22;
4898  if( member_name == "turn_last_touched" ) {
4899  last_touched = time_point( jv.get_int() );
4900  } else if( member_name == "temperature" ) {
4901  temperature_mod = jv.get_int();
4902  } else if( member_name == "terrain" ) {
4903  // TODO: try block around this to error out if we come up short?
4904  JsonArray terrain_json = jv;
4905  // Small duplication here so that the update check is only performed once
4906  if( rubpow_update ) {
4907  item rock = item( "rock", calendar::turn_zero );
4908  item chunk = item( "steel_chunk", calendar::turn_zero );
4909  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY; j++ ) {
4910  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX; i++ ) {
4911  const ter_str_id tid( terrain_json.next_string() );
4912 
4913  if( tid == ter_t_rubble ) {
4914  m->ter[i][j] = ter_t_dirt;
4915  m->frn[i][j] = furn_id( "f_rubble" );
4916  m->itm[i][j].insert( rock );
4917  m->itm[i][j].insert( rock );
4918  } else if( tid == ter_t_wreckage ) {
4919  m->ter[i][j] = ter_t_dirt;
4920  m->frn[i][j] = furn_id( "f_wreckage" );
4921  m->itm[i][j].insert( chunk );
4922  m->itm[i][j].insert( chunk );
4923  } else if( tid == ter_t_ash ) {
4924  m->ter[i][j] = ter_t_dirt;
4925  m->frn[i][j] = furn_id( "f_ash" );
4926  } else if( tid == ter_t_pwr_sb_support_l ) {
4927  m->ter[i][j] = ter_t_support_l;
4928  } else if( tid == ter_t_pwr_sb_switchgear_l ) {
4929  m->ter[i][j] = ter_t_switchgear_l;
4930  } else if( tid == ter_t_pwr_sb_switchgear_s ) {
4931  m->ter[i][j] = ter_t_switchgear_s;
4932  } else {
4933  m->ter[i][j] = tid.id();
4934  }
4935  }
4936  }
4937  } else {
4938  // terrain is encoded using simple RLE
4939  int remaining = 0;
4940  int_id<ter_t> iid_ter;
4941  int_id<furn_t> iid_furn;
4942  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY; j++ ) {
4943  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(modernize-loop-convert)
4944  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX; i++ ) {
4945  if( !remaining ) {
4946  JsonValue terrain_entry = terrain_json.next_value();
4947  auto migrate_terstr = [&]( ter_str_id terstr ) {
4948  if( auto it = ter_migrations.find( terstr ); it != ter_migrations.end() ) {
4949  terstr = it->second.first;
4950  if( it->second.second != furn_str_id::NULL_ID() ) {
4951  iid_furn = it->second.second.id();
4952  }
4953  }
4954  if( terstr.is_valid() ) {
4955  iid_ter = terstr.id();
4956  } else {
4957  debugmsg( "invalid ter_str_id '%s'", terstr.c_str() );
4958  iid_ter = ter_t_dirt;
4959  }
4960  };
4961  if( terrain_entry.test_string() ) {
4962  migrate_terstr( ter_str_id( terrain_entry.get_string() ) );
4963  } else if( terrain_entry.test_array() ) {
4964  JsonArray terrain_rle = terrain_entry;
4965  migrate_terstr( ter_str_id( terrain_rle.next_string() ) );
4966  remaining = terrain_rle.next_int() - 1;
4967  if( terrain_rle.size() > 2 ) {
4968  terrain_rle.throw_error( "Too many values for terrain RLE" );
4969  }
4970  } else {
4971  debugmsg( "Mapbuffer terrain data is corrupt, expected string or array." );
4972  }
4973  } else {
4974  --remaining;
4975  }
4976  m->ter[i][j] = iid_ter;
4977  if( iid_furn ) {
4978  m->frn[i][j] = iid_furn;
4979  }
4980  }
4981  }
4982  if( remaining ) {
4983  debugmsg( "Mapbuffer terrain data is corrupt, tile data remaining." );
4984  }
4985  }
4986  } else if( member_name == "radiation" ) {
4987  int rad_cell = 0;
4988  JsonArray radiation_rle = jv;
4989  while( radiation_rle.has_more() ) {
4990  int rad_strength = radiation_rle.next_int();
4991  int rad_num = radiation_rle.next_int();
4992  for( int i = 0; i < rad_num; ++i ) {
4993  if( rad_cell < SEEX * SEEY ) {
4994  set_radiation( { rad_cell % SEEX, rad_cell / SEEX }, rad_strength );
4995  rad_cell++;
4996  }
4997  }
4998  }
4999  } else if( member_name == "furniture" ) {
5000  int_id<ter_t> iid_ter;
5001  int_id<furn_t> iid_furn;
5002  JsonArray furniture_json = jv;
5003  for( JsonArray furniture_entry : furniture_json ) {
5004  int i = furniture_entry.next_int();
5005  int j = furniture_entry.next_int();
5006  furn_str_id furnstr( furniture_entry.next_string() );
5007  if( auto it = furn_migrations.find( furnstr ); it != furn_migrations.end() ) {
